article.headline: California Riverside 64, Eastern Illinois 55
article.story: AMES, Iowa (AP) -- Larry Cunningham scored 18 points and Justin Bell had 10 of his 13 in the final 2:38, lifting UC Riverside to a 64-55 victory over Eastern Illinois on Saturday night. UC Riverside (1-1) rallied from a 22-10 deficit by scoring the final 11 points of the first half, then went on a 10-2 run early in the second half to take the lead for good at 35-28 on the second night of the round-robin Cyclone Challenge at Iowa State. After Eastern Illinois (0-2) drew to 35-32 on Julio Anthony's only basket of the game, UC Riverside answered with a 12-2 burst to regain control. Cunningham, who shot 6-for-9, made a jumper from the right wing and followed with a 3-pointer to key that run. Bell hit a 3-pointer to make it 57-48, then went 7-for-8 at the free-throw line to wrap it up for the Highlanders, who didn't get their first victory last season until Jan. 2. B.J. Visman added 10 points for UC Riverside, which shot 56 percent (14-for-25) in the second half. Jon'Tee Willhite led Eastern Illinois with 14 points.
